Description
OxyPriva is a privacy-first verification tool for Web3 communities. It allows members to securely prove ownership of assets (NFTs, tokens, or passes) to unlock exclusive Discord roles—without exposing their wallet address or linking it directly to their social identity.
This solves one of the biggest problems in community verification today: members want exclusivity and proof of ownership, but they don’t want to compromise their privacy by revealing their wallet activity.
SL Integration
OxyPriva integrates with the Soundness Layer (SL) to ensure that verification is both secure and privacy-preserving.

### 1. Verification Process
A user privately connects their wallet on OxyPriva.
A Zero-Knowledge Proof (ZK-Proof) is generated via SL, confirming ownership of the required asset without revealing the wallet address.
The ZK-Proof is sent to OxyPriva’s Discord bot.
The bot grants the appropriate role automatically.

### 2. Data Privacy
Wallet addresses are never stored or revealed.
Only the proof is passed to Discord, ensuring identity and financial activity remain separate.

### 3. Benefits of SL Integration
Privacy: Wallet details are never shared.
Security: Proofs prevent fraudulent role claims.
Transparency: Anyone can verify the proof without accessing sensitive user data.
Simplicity: One-click verification with automated Discord role assignment.

